---
import Link from "@components/Link.astro";
import ChevronLeft from "@icons/ChevronLeft.astro";
import Layout from "@layouts/Layout.astro";
import P from "@components/P.astro";
import ArrowUpRight from "@icons/ArrowUpRight.astro";
---

<Layout title="Shlok Desai | Peer Mentor CS 544">
  <div class="flex justify-center max-w-7xl gap-x-16 mx-auto px-4">
    <div class="w-40 hidden xl:block">
      <button
        onclick="history.back();"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-x-1 border-b border-gray9
              hover:border-gray11 hover:text-gray12 transition-colors w-fit
              tracking-wide font-light text-gray12 text-base"
      >
        <ChevronLeft size={16} />
         cd . .
      </button>
    </div>

    <div id="main" class="max-w-2xl w-full">
      <div class="flex items-center justify-between">
        <h1 class="text-gray12 tracking-wider">
          Peer Mentor for CS 544{" "}
          <span class="text-gray11 font-light">@ UW-Madison</span>
        </h1>

        <button
          onclick="history.back();"
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-x-1 border-b border-gray9
              hover:border-gray11 hover:text-gray12 transition-colors w-fit
              tracking-wide font-light text-gray12 text-base xl:hidden"
        >
          <ChevronLeft size={16} />
           cd . .
        </button>
      </div>

      <span class="text-gray11 font-light text-sm mt-4 block">
        Madison, WI â€¢ 04/2023 - Present
      </span>

      <P className="mt-8">
        CS 544 is The University of Wisconsin-Madison's latest class on Big Data
        Systems. I took this class during it's very first offering under
        <Link variant="primary" href="https://tyler.caraza-harter.com/">
          Tyler R. Caraza-Harter
          <ArrowUpRight size={16} />
        </Link>.
      </P>

      <P className="mt-4">
        In this class, students are taught how to deploy and use distributed
        systems to store and analyze large datasets. Unstructured and structured
        approaches to storage is covered. Analysis involves learning new query
        languages, processing streaming data, and training machine learning
        models. Systems covered include Docker, PyTorch, HDFS, Spark, Cassandra,
        Kafka, and more.
      </P>

      <P className="mt-8">Responsibilites:</P>

      <ul class="mt-4 list-disc text-gray11">
        <li>
          <P>Help students understand and absorb course material.</P>
        </li>
        <li>
          <P>
            Help students debug code and brainstorm solutions for their projects
            (90% of my job since this class is extremley application heavy).
          </P>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <div class="pt-4"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="w-40 hidden xl:block"></div>
  </div>
</Layout>
